FBIS3-60855 "jptot001__l94103" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Girls Released; Hijackers May Fly to Dagestan LD2412165093 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 24 Dec 93 LD2412165093 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] According to information available now, the helicopter with the hostages and terrorists on board is at the Mineralnyye Vody airport. The helicopter is being refueled. [passage omitted] Kazis Zukhrabov, member of the Dagestan Interior Ministry press service, has informed us that the republic's interior and security ministries personnel have been on alert since yesterday evening. According to him, if the helicopter arrives in Makhachkala all the necessary measures will be undertaken to release the hostages through talks with the terrorists. [Moscow ITAR-TASS in English at 1620 GMT on 24 December in a Moscow-datelined item carries the following related report: ["All the girls from the group of teenagers kidnapped in Rostov-on-Don (southern Russia) on Thursday were released by the gunmen in the airport of Mineralnyye Vody on Friday in exchange for a ransom of $10 million, an official from Russia's State Committee on Emergencies told ITAR-TASS.]
